label: DSS ID
notesForProvider: Does DSS ID mean something different in Kenya and Gambia/Mali. In the former it seems to indicate unique participant but not in the latter.

label: Caretaker relationship to participant
definition: Is interviewee a primary caretaker of the participant?

label: Reason interview not conducted
codebookValues: 1="Primary caretaker not available", 2="Refused", 3="Moved away", 4="Child died more than 7 days ago (including today)", 5="Cannot locate child", 9="Other"

label: Primary caretaker's education level
codebookValues: 1="No formal schooling", 2="Less than primary", 3="Completed secondary", 4="Post-secondary", 5="Completed primary", 6="Religious education only", 7="Don't know"

label: Persons living in house
definition: How many people have been living regularly in your household for the past 6 months?

label: Animal-drawn cart
definition: Do you have an animal-drawn cart?
codebookDescription: Do you have an animal-drawn cart

label: Breast milk
definition: Does the child normally take breast milk?

label: Plain water
definition: Does the child normally drink water?

label: Other foods or drinks
definition: Does the child normally take other foods or drinks?

label: Diarrhea case during the last 7 days, caregiver report
definition: Did the child have diarrhea in the last week?

label: Child days since diarrhea
definition: How many days ago did the diarrhea start?

label: Diarrheal episode duration (days)
definition: How many days did the diarrhea last?

label: Max loose stools at episode
definition: What were the maximum number of loose stools in one day?
codebookValues: 1="3", 2="4 to 5", 3="6 to 10", 4="More than 10 times per day"

label: Measured fever of at least 38C or parental perception
Unable to drink or drank poorly

definition: On the worst day, how many times did the child vomit?

label: Days vomiting during diarrheal illness
definition: How many days did the child have vomiting?

label: Amount offered to drink during diarrheal episode
definition:
While the child had diarrhea, how much did you offer
him/her to drink, including breast milk?
codebookValues: 1="More than usual, 2="Usual", 3="Somewhat less than usual", 4="Much less than usual", 5="Nothing to drink"

label: Amount offered to eat during diarrheal episode
definition:
While the child had diarrhea, how much did you offer
the child to eat?
codebookValues: 1="More than usual, 2="Usual", 3="Less than usual", 4="Nothing to eat"

label: Seek outside care
definition:
Did you seek care for the child's diarrhea outside your home
home?

label: Friend or relative
definition: Sought care from friend or relative

definition: Sought care from center of 1st choice

definition: Sought care from center of 2nd choice

definition: Sought care from center of 3rd choice

label: Bought a remedy or drug
definition: Bought remedy or medicine at the shop

definition: Did the clinical team advise that the child be hospitalized?
